```

**Key points:**

- **`GetTypeInfo<T>()`** – gives you a `JsonTypeInfo<T>` without manual casting. Throws if the resolver can't handle `T`.
- **`TryGetTypeInfo<T>(out JsonTypeInfo<T>?)`** – the no-throw probe you asked for. Returns `false` when the resolver doesn't know the type (e.g., a source-gen context that only covers certain types).

Both are new in .NET 11 on `JsonSerializerOptions`.
